 wrong note is an omen, a crime, or the first syllable of a very old name.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\n        \"Calibrate three organ mouths on the Gale Organ Cliffs using the Rite-Striker to capture their tones, braving the wind-slaps and the narrow training ledges without altering the pipes.\",\n        \"Ascend to the Aeric Aerie and retrieve last week’s sealed horn-logs under proper rite, ensuring the wax-sigils remain unbroken and documented.\",\n        \"Consult Cantor Roa Mestri privately about a missing set of wind-tones and record any details or suspicions without drawing public attention.\",\n        \"Record the anomalous three-note pattern into the Moonshard Lantern so its cold lens remembers the braid of sound for comparison in the Archive.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Ysil Aer\", \"lines\": \"The cliff sings what the city refuses to say, and it sings to those who will stop and be small enough to hear. Do you hear it, child of the hollow, three notes braided under the ordinary breath like a pulse that has learned patience? We will be accused of withholding omens again if we act on a whisper, and there are those who would make any whisper a cudgel to beat the Temple down. Yet if we wait for thunder and proof that bruises the eye, the thunder may be falling men and the proof a widow’s breath. Go with the Rite-Striker and the humility we swore, and do not strike a horn unless the wind itself begs you to. Bring me the wind’s memory, not rumor, and bring me the shape of its silence where it does not sing. If you must choose between being called a fool and letting a child go unwarned, be my fool and I will be yours at Spinegate.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Aerin Rell\", \"lines\": \"I hear it, High Cantor, and it scratches the mind the way glass scratches rope, slowly and certain if left unattended. It catches like grit in a line, and I have learned the cost of letting grit stay under tension. I will find whether the false n